13
00:00:31,260 --> 00:00:33,220
In fact, we began in January,

14
00:00:33,220 --> 00:00:35,500
so we didn't do it every Wednesday evening.

15
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,740
But we started January 29th,

16
00:00:37,740 --> 00:00:40,380
and we've had the opportunity to look at a number

17
00:00:40,380 --> 00:00:44,000
of the names of God that he gives to us in his word.

18
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,860
And we mentioned that God, he is infinite, right?

19
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:48,180
And we are finite.

20
00:00:48,180 --> 00:00:51,340
We understand that he transcends us,

21
00:00:51,340 --> 00:00:54,619
that his ways are not our ways, that he's far above

22
00:00:54,619 --> 00:00:57,459
all that we could even begin to comprehend.

23
00:00:57,500 --> 00:01:00,500
And so we find that through the Old Testament,

24
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:01,939
we find also in the New Testament,

25
00:01:01,939 --> 00:01:04,459
there are many names that are ascribed to our God.

26
00:01:04,459 --> 00:01:07,099
And through those names, he's communicating to us

27
00:01:07,099 --> 00:01:10,239
certain aspects of his attribute, his character,

28
00:01:10,239 --> 00:01:13,220
and helping us to be able to understand those things.

29
00:01:13,220 --> 00:01:15,940
As we come to Judges chapter six this evening,

30
00:01:15,940 --> 00:01:17,860
we'll look at a name that's given to us.

31
00:01:17,860 --> 00:01:20,099
And that name, I'll read verse 23 and 24.

32
00:01:20,099 --> 00:01:21,819
We'll grab some of the context

33
00:01:21,819 --> 00:01:24,459
as we go through the message this evening.

34
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:25,860
But if you will look in verse 23,

35
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:28,779
the Lord said unto him, that's speaking to Gideon,

36
00:01:28,779 --> 00:01:32,819
peace be unto thee, fear not, thou shalt not die.

37
00:01:32,819 --> 00:01:34,180
Gideon thought that he would die.

38
00:01:34,180 --> 00:01:36,220
He mentions that as we look at the text

39
00:01:36,220 --> 00:01:39,019
and grab the context of it, because he says,

40
00:01:39,019 --> 00:01:41,220
in verse number 22, I have seen an angel

41
00:01:41,220 --> 00:01:42,339
of the Lord face to face.

42
00:01:42,339 --> 00:01:43,300
So he thought he would die.

43
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:46,339
And the Lord said unto him, peace be unto thee,

44
00:01:46,339 --> 00:01:48,019
fear not, thou shalt not die.

45
00:01:48,019 --> 00:01:52,300
Verse 24, then Gideon built an altar there unto the Lord

46
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:55,819
and called it Jehovah Shalom unto this day.

47
00:01:56,660 --> 00:01:59,459
It is yet an ophrah of the Abizurites.

48
00:01:59,459 --> 00:02:01,819
And so as we look at this text of scripture,

49
00:02:01,819 --> 00:02:05,500
God reveals to us a name that's mentioned really here

50
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:08,580
in its exact context, Jehovah Shalom.

51
00:02:08,580 --> 00:02:12,139
And many of us, we are familiar with that word Shalom.

52
00:02:12,139 --> 00:02:14,339
If you travel the Middle East, you'll hear in Israel,

53
00:02:14,339 --> 00:02:16,699
you hear that very regularly as a greeting

54
00:02:16,699 --> 00:02:19,580
and also as you depart from having conversation

55
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:20,619
with one another.

56
00:02:20,619 --> 00:02:23,660
And so as we look at this name of God in verse 24,

57
00:02:23,660 --> 00:02:26,100
I've just titled the message Jehovah Shalom.

58
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:28,820
And it means the Lord is peace.

59
00:02:28,820 --> 00:02:30,779
And many of us are familiar with the life

60
00:02:30,779 --> 00:02:31,899
and ministry of Gideon.

61
00:02:31,899 --> 00:02:35,220
And we find that here as he builds this altar in verse 24,

62
00:02:35,220 --> 00:02:38,220
that that's the name in which he gives the altar.

63
00:02:38,220 --> 00:02:40,059
Let me share with you a definition of peace

64
00:02:40,059 --> 00:02:41,779
that I really like.

65
00:02:41,779 --> 00:02:43,460
And here's the definition.

66
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:46,300
And I really think there's two parts of the definition.

67
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:49,619
It really helps us to see the two aspects of peace

68
00:02:49,619 --> 00:02:51,419
that we see within the scriptures.

69
00:02:51,539 --> 00:02:55,820
But here's the definition, the tranquil state of a soul

70
00:02:55,820 --> 00:02:59,940
assured of its salvation through Christ.

71
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:04,940
And this evening, if you have assurance of your salvation,

72
00:03:05,179 --> 00:03:06,699
you have that peace.

73
00:03:07,779 --> 00:03:10,419
There's a peace that comes with that.

74
00:03:10,419 --> 00:03:14,940
I would say that that's describing for us peace with God.

75
00:03:14,940 --> 00:03:17,619
And we see that phraseology in Romans chapter five.

76
00:03:17,619 --> 00:03:19,259
We'll look at that in just a little while.

77
00:03:19,380 --> 00:03:22,020
But then the definition goes on to say this.

78
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:27,020
And so fearing nothing from God and content

79
00:03:27,259 --> 00:03:32,259
with its earthly lot of whatsoever sort that is.

80
00:03:33,259 --> 00:03:36,059
And I think the second half of that definition

81
00:03:36,059 --> 00:03:39,380
really is describing for us the peace of God.

82
00:03:39,380 --> 00:03:42,160
And what a blessing to have peace with God,

83
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:44,179
but then we understand the peace of God.

84
00:03:44,179 --> 00:03:47,160
We often make that reference in that distinction

85
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,979
as we go through the New Testament

86
00:03:49,580 --> 00:03:51,020
and look at those various phraseologies.

87
00:03:51,020 --> 00:03:53,139
And we'll look at a few of those things this evening.

88
00:03:53,139 --> 00:03:55,179
But as we look at our text of scripture here this evening

89
00:03:55,179 --> 00:03:57,460
and look at this name that God provides

90
00:03:57,460 --> 00:04:01,979
and as this Gideon, as he builds this altar

91
00:04:01,979 --> 00:04:04,220
and he names it Jehovah Shalom.

92
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:05,580
If you're taking notes this evening,

93
00:04:05,580 --> 00:04:07,259
I want you to notice with me first of all,

94
00:04:07,259 --> 00:04:11,220
the absence of peace, the absence of peace.

95
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:14,139
And we see it specifically, we'll look at two aspects

96
00:04:14,139 --> 00:04:16,380
of this message as we go through with each of the points.

97
00:04:16,420 --> 00:04:19,260
But I want you to see first the absence of peace

98
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:21,220
for Gideon and for Israel.

99
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:23,140
The Bible begins in chapter number six

100
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:24,619
and it says this in verse number one,

101
00:04:24,619 --> 00:04:28,500
and the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord

102
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:31,260
and the Lord delivered them into the hand of Midian

103
00:04:31,260 --> 00:04:35,859
seven years and the hand of Midian prevailed against Israel.

104
00:04:35,859 --> 00:04:37,980
Because of the Midianites, the children of Israel

105
00:04:37,980 --> 00:04:41,339
made them the dens, which are in the mountains

106
00:04:41,339 --> 00:04:43,140
and caves and strongholds.

107
00:04:43,140 --> 00:04:45,980
And so it was when Israel had sown

108
00:04:46,579 --> 00:04:48,380
that the Midianites came up and the Amalekites

109
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:51,339
and the children of the East, even they came up against them

110
00:04:51,339 --> 00:04:53,980
and they encamped against them and destroyed

111
00:04:53,980 --> 00:04:57,660
the increase of the earth till thou come unto Gaza

112
00:04:57,660 --> 00:04:59,940
and left no sustenance for Israel,

113
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:02,899
neither sheep nor ox nor ass for they came up

114
00:05:02,899 --> 00:05:04,859
with their cattle in their tents

115
00:05:04,859 --> 00:05:07,899
and they came as grasshoppers for multitude

116
00:05:07,899 --> 00:05:12,100
for both they and their camels were without number

117
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:14,779
and they entered into the land to destroy it.

118
00:05:14,779 --> 00:05:17,140
And Israel was greatly impoverished

119
00:05:17,140 --> 00:05:20,179
because of the Midianites and the children of Israel

120
00:05:20,179 --> 00:05:22,940
cried unto the Lord.

121
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:25,940
That's the setting for Judges chapter number six

122
00:05:25,940 --> 00:05:28,200
as we're introduced in just a few verses

123
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,739
past what I read there in those first six verses

124
00:05:30,739 --> 00:05:33,100
were eventually introduced to Gideon,

125
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:35,299
the one who builds the altar and the verses

126
00:05:35,299 --> 00:05:37,420
that we looked at by way of introduction.

127
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:40,459
But we find that as we look at the situation

128
00:05:40,459 --> 00:05:44,559
that Gideon and Israel are dealing with,

129
00:05:45,339 --> 00:05:46,440
that there's an absence of peace,

130
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:49,079
there's great turmoil, there's great conflict.

131
00:05:49,079 --> 00:05:51,000
The Bible says that they entered into the land

132
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,799
at the end of verse number five to destroy it.

133
00:05:52,799 --> 00:05:57,320
The Bible tells us that when they were trying to go forth

134
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:59,679
and it says, and when Israel had sown

135
00:05:59,679 --> 00:06:02,480
and when they're coming to the place where they would reap

136
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:04,880
the Midianites and the Amalekites,

137
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:06,440
they would come and they would try to take

138
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:07,600
all of that substance.

139
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:10,679
And it says that they left no sustenance for Israel,

140
00:06:10,679 --> 00:06:14,040
neither sheep nor ox nor ass at the end of verse number four.

141
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,200
And so what does Israel do?

142
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,959
Well, the Bible says they cried unto the Lord

143
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,640
at the end of verse number six.

144
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:21,239
And there's an absence of peace for Gideon

145
00:06:21,239 --> 00:06:24,440
and for the people of God in this text of scripture.

146
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:26,299
We find that as we consider the truth

147
00:06:26,299 --> 00:06:29,519
of an absence of peace and we see it contextually here

148
00:06:29,519 --> 00:06:31,359
with the circumstances and situation

149
00:06:31,359 --> 00:06:32,739
in which they're dealing with,

150
00:06:32,739 --> 00:06:35,320
I would submit to you this evening

151
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:39,040
that there's an absence of peace with regard to humanity.

152
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:42,959
Generally speaking, the Bible says in Isaiah 48 in verse 22,

153
00:06:42,959 --> 00:06:45,799
there is no peace, saith the Lord, unto the wicked.

154
00:06:45,799 --> 00:06:48,760
And we see that repeated again in Isaiah 57.

155
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:51,200
And we find that the world,

156
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,540
as we would even understand in our own lives

157
00:06:53,540 --> 00:06:55,040
and considering that definition

158
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:57,079
that we use by way of introduction,

159
00:06:57,079 --> 00:07:00,859
that prior to salvation, I had no peace.

160
00:07:00,859 --> 00:07:04,440
And the reality is that oftentimes we'll speak

161
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:08,399
of the time of before we trusted Christ

162
00:07:08,399 --> 00:07:11,600
of having no peace and no hope and no direction.

163
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:16,600
And the reality is that humanity for lost people,

164
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,920
there is an absence of peace.

165
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:22,519
And you experienced that before you got saved.

166
00:07:22,519 --> 00:07:24,420
If you're here this evening and you're not saved,

167
00:07:24,420 --> 00:07:27,119
you don't know the Lord Jesus Christ, your personal savior,

168
00:07:27,119 --> 00:07:29,279
you too at this moment would understand

169
00:07:29,279 --> 00:07:31,359
that absence of peace.

170
00:07:31,359 --> 00:07:33,880
And so many people are trying to find peace

171
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:35,040
in so many different areas.

172
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:38,399
They think that peace is found in the absence of trouble.

173
00:07:38,399 --> 00:07:41,279
They think that if there could just be a,

174
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:42,839
my problems are dealt with,

175
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:45,839
but the reality is that having peace with God

176
00:07:45,839 --> 00:07:49,119
only comes through the Lord Jesus Christ.

177
00:07:49,119 --> 00:07:51,040
And we'll deal with that in just a moment.

178
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,200
But we see with humanity, I mentioned Isaiah 48,

179
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,559
but look at the New Testament, if you will,

180
00:07:54,559 --> 00:07:55,480
the book of Romans.

181
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:58,160
We'll look at a couple of verses in Romans

182
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:59,640
and then also in the book of Ephesians.

183
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:02,679
Look in Romans first with me in chapter number five.

184
00:08:02,679 --> 00:08:06,420
And again, dealing with this absence of peace,

185
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:08,839
Gideon experienced it.

186
00:08:08,839 --> 00:08:10,679
The nation of Israel experienced it

187
00:08:10,679 --> 00:08:12,519
in Judges chapter number six.

188
00:08:12,519 --> 00:08:15,679
And we find that the announcement from the Lord

189
00:08:15,679 --> 00:08:18,119
in verse 23 is peace.

190
00:08:18,119 --> 00:08:21,279
And then he builds an altar and he names it Jehovah Shalom,

191
00:08:21,279 --> 00:08:22,959
the Lord is peace.

192
00:08:22,959 --> 00:08:25,279
And we find that in Romans chapter number five,

193
00:08:25,279 --> 00:08:26,760
begin looking in verse number eight,

194
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:29,880
the Bible says, but God commended his love toward us

195
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:33,880
in that while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.

196
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:37,599
Much more than being now justified by his blood,

197
00:08:37,599 --> 00:08:40,200
we shall be saved from wrath through him.

198
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:44,320
For if when we were enemies, you see that?

199
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,960
When we were enemies, we were against God,

200
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:50,320
we were reconciled to God by the death of his son,

201
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:53,440
much more being reconciled, we shall be saved by his life.

202
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,780
And we talked about in the book of 2 Corinthians

203
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:58,320
in recent weeks, as we've studied through the book,

204
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:00,400
that ministry of reconciliation

205
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:03,140
and the fact that we have been reconciled

206
00:09:03,140 --> 00:09:07,000
then is entrusted to us the ministry of reconciliation.

207
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,320
And what was the need?

208
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:10,400
Why was there a need to be reconciled?

209
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:13,960
Because we were at variance, we were at enemy of God,

210
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:18,919
we are sin separated us from God and we had no peace.

211
00:09:18,919 --> 00:09:21,460
And there's an absence of peace.

212
00:09:21,460 --> 00:09:24,599
We find in Ephesians chapter number two,

213
00:09:24,599 --> 00:09:27,719
the Bible tells us and we'll look at this passage

214
00:09:27,719 --> 00:09:29,200
a couple of times this evening,

215
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,719
I wanna look at just verses 11 and 12,

216
00:09:31,719 --> 00:09:34,539
as we consider this thought of the absence of peace.

217
00:09:34,539 --> 00:09:37,340
Notice what the Bible says in Ephesians two,

218
00:09:37,340 --> 00:09:38,539
beginning in verse number 11.

219
00:09:38,539 --> 00:09:42,200
He says, wherefore, remember, he's writing to save people,

220
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:44,059
the church at Ephesus is the church

221
00:09:44,059 --> 00:09:45,739
that's being written this epistle.

222
00:09:45,739 --> 00:09:47,340
He's writing to save people.

223
00:09:47,340 --> 00:09:50,580
He talks about in the beginning of chapter number two,

224
00:09:50,580 --> 00:09:52,900
about their conversion,

225
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:54,659
for by grace are you saved through faith.

226
00:09:54,659 --> 00:09:55,979
He mentions in verse number eight,

227
00:09:55,979 --> 00:09:57,659
just a couple of verses earlier,

228
00:09:57,659 --> 00:09:59,140
but then he says in verse number 11,

229
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,479
wherefore, remember,

230
00:10:00,479 --> 00:10:07,479
You know, there are times in which we, too, remember what we were, the state we were in before we got saved.

231
00:10:07,479 --> 00:10:14,479
And notice what he says, that ye, being in time past Gentiles in the flesh, who are called uncircumcision,

232
00:10:14,479 --> 00:10:21,479
by that which is called the circumcision in the flesh made by hands, that at that time ye were without Christ,

233
00:10:21,479 --> 00:10:27,479
being aliens from the commonwealth of Israel and strangers from the covenants of promise,

234
00:10:27,479 --> 00:10:32,479
having no hope and without God in the world.

235
00:10:32,479 --> 00:10:36,479
The Bible doesn't specifically say in verses 11 and 12 that we have no peace,

236
00:10:36,479 --> 00:10:42,479
but I do not believe that it's a stretch for us to say that there's an absence of peace prior to salvation,

237
00:10:42,479 --> 00:10:47,479
for we find in just a couple of verses the Bible says that He is our peace in verse number 14,

238
00:10:47,479 --> 00:10:49,479
and we'll look at that in just a moment.

239
00:10:49,479 --> 00:10:55,479
But we find that as we look at this passage of Scripture and dealing with the name of God, Jehovah Shalom,

240
00:10:55,479 --> 00:10:59,479
and the Lord is peace, and we see that Gideon and the people of Israel,

241
00:10:59,479 --> 00:11:04,479
they were dealing with some real situations, circumstances where there was no peace,

242
00:11:04,479 --> 00:11:10,479
there was turmoil, there was hostility, there was destruction, and they had no peace.

243
00:11:10,479 --> 00:11:15,479
And then Gideon has this experience where the Lord appears to him and says,

244
00:11:15,479 --> 00:11:22,479
Gideon, thou mighty man of valor, and Gideon is now thinking that he's going to die,

245
00:11:22,479 --> 00:11:27,479
and the Lord says, peace, peace, and he makes that altar.

246
00:11:27,479 --> 00:11:30,479
The Lord is peace, Jehovah Shalom.

247
00:11:30,479 --> 00:11:35,479
See, for us this evening, we've experienced, if you're saved tonight, you've been,

248
00:11:35,479 --> 00:11:42,479
you can recall when you were lost, and you can recall, you can know when you had no peace.

249
00:11:42,479 --> 00:11:49,479
And the reality is that there's many that are around us today that there's still an absence of peace.

250
00:11:49,479 --> 00:11:51,479
There's an absence of peace.

251
00:11:51,479 --> 00:11:55,479
